## What the specialists returned and how it shaped the response

**Technical Fit — HIGH fit.** Full fit on every non-negotiable: native Power BI DirectQuery for 600 users, 3× ingest headroom (250K vs 80K eps peak), per-table EU residency, lakehouse on Delta/Iceberg/Parquet, proven 16-week Teradata migration. Two honest calls I carried through: 99.99% is a paid active-active tier (not baseline 99.95%), and query-at-scale needs a tiering/caching story for 280TB.

**Competitive Intel — Fabric is the primary threat** ("free with E5"). The playbook: don't fight on Power BI ownership — own execution and TCO. Lead with Initech (IoT peer that beat Fabric on real-time SLA) and the Globex 3-year TCO win. Baked into Section 3's competitor table.

**Pricing — compete on TCO, not discount theatre.** $720K/yr Enterprise list; offer 20%, improvable to 25% for the full 3+2 — Acme's 35% breaches our ceiling (and chasing it repeats the Pied Piper loss). Net 60 not 90, capped escalator not a 5-year freeze, reject MFN. Rendered as a transparent 5-year schedule (~$576K Yr1, ~$3.06M total).

**Legal — five blockers with clean counters.** Cap liability at 24 months' fees (drop fines/reputational indemnity), subprocessor list+notice, SLA service credits instead of instant termination, retain platform IP with a licence-back to Acme (the Stark precedent), and audit down to 1×/yr with notice.

## Judgment calls I made
- **Framed it as a client-facing proposal**, so internal-only strategy (walk-away thresholds, "poisonous clause" language) stayed out — the substance is presented as constructive negotiating positions Acme would actually receive.
- **Priced the 99.99% add-on explicitly** rather than burying it, per Technical Fit's warning that evaluators may treat it as pass/fail.
- No dedicated docx/BTS branding SKILL.md existed, so I built the branding directly (navy/teal palette, styled tables, cover, running header/footer) via python-docx.

The document is ready to submit to procurement@acme-synthetic.example ahead of the 26 May deadline.

